					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Reg=
ion between two concentric circles</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other us=
es, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annulus_(disambiguation)" =
class=3D"mw-redirect mw-disambig" title=3D"Annulus (disambiguation)">Annulu=
s</a>.</div>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Annulus_area.svg" class=3D"mw-file-description" tit=
le=3D"An annulus"><img alt=3D"An annulus" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.o=
rg/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Annulus_area.svg/250px-Annulus_area.svg.png=
" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"150" height=3D"150" class=3D"mw-file-element"=
 data-file-width=3D"402" data-file-height=3D"402"></a><figcaption>An annulu=
s</figcaption></figure>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Mamikon_annulus_area_visualisation.svg" class=
=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia=
/commons/thumb/e/e5/Mamikon_annulus_area_visualisation.svg/250px-Mamikon_an=
nulus_area_visualisation.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"190" height=
=3D"380" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"512" data-file-height=
=3D"1024"></a><figcaption>Illustration of Mamikon's <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_calculus" title=3D"Visual calculus">visual calculu=
s</a> method showing that the areas of two annuli with the same chord lengt=
h are the same regardless of inner and outer radii.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annulus_(mathem=
atics)#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup></figcaption></figure>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathem=
atics">mathematics</a>, an <b>annulus</b> (<abbr title=3D"plural">pl.</abbr=
>: <b>annuli</b> or <b>annuluses</b>) is the region between two concentric =
circles. Informally, it is shaped like a ring or a <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Washer_(hardware)" title=3D"Washer (hardware)">hardware wa=
sher</a>. The word "annulus" is borrowed from the <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Latin" title=3D"Latin">Latin</a> word <i>anulus</i> or <i>a=
nnulus</i> meaning 'little ring'. The adjectival form is <i><b>annular</b><=
/i> (as in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annular_eclipse" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Annular eclipse">annular eclipse</a>).
</p><p>The open annulus is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homeomo=
rphism" title=3D"Homeomorphism">topologically equivalent</a> to both the op=
en <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cylinder" title=3D"Cylinder">cy=
linder</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>S</i><sup>1</sup> =C3=97 (0,1)</span>=
 and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punctured_plane" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Punctured plane">punctured plane</a>.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Area">Area</h2><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAnnulus_(mathematics)&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Area"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The area of an annulus is the difference in the areas of the larger <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circle" title=3D"Circle">circle</a> of=
 radius <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span> and the smaller one of radi=
us <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>r</i></span>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e A=3D\pi R^{2}-\pi r^{2}=3D\pi \left(R^{2}-r^{2}\right)=3D\pi (R+r)(R-r).}=
">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <msup>
          <mi>R</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <msup>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>R</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <msup>
              <mi>r</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A=3D\pi R^{2}=
-\pi r^{2}=3D\pi \left(R^{2}-r^{2}\right)=3D\pi (R+r)(R-r).}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d29025b73d7d745a4d573cae64bc5718f8363f47" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:49.978ex; height:3.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
=3D\pi R^{2}-\pi r^{2}=3D\pi \left(R^{2}-r^{2}\right)=3D\pi (R+r)(R-r).}"><=
/span></dd></dl>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Annuli_with_same_area_around_unit_regular_pol=
ygons.svg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimed=
ia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Annuli_with_same_area_around_unit_regul=
ar_polygons.svg/250px-Annuli_with_same_area_around_unit_regular_polygons.sv=
g.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"200" height=3D"267" class=3D"mw-file-ele=
ment" data-file-width=3D"512" data-file-height=3D"683"></a><figcaption>As a=
 corollary of the chord formula, the area bounded by the <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circumcircle" title=3D"Circumcircle">circumcircle</a=
> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incircle" class=3D"mw-redire=
ct" title=3D"Incircle">incircle</a> of every unit convex regular polygon is=
 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=80</span>/4<=
/figcaption></figure>
<p>The area of an annulus is determined by the length of the longest <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line_segment" title=3D"Line segment">lin=
e segment</a> within the annulus, which is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Chord_(geometry)" title=3D"Chord (geometry)">chord</a> tangent=
 to the inner circle, <span class=3D"texhtml">2<i>d</i></span> in the accom=
panying diagram. That can be shown using the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem" title=3D"Pythagorean theorem">Pythagorean t=
heorem</a> since this line is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tang=
ent" title=3D"Tangent">tangent</a> to the smaller circle and perpendicular =
to its radius at that point, so <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>d</i></span> and=
 <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>r</i></span> are sides of a right-angled triang=
le with hypotenuse <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span>, and the area of=
 the annulus is given by
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e A=3D\pi \left(R^{2}-r^{2}\right)=3D\pi d^{2}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>R</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <msup>
              <mi>r</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
