lt;|z-a|&lt;R.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>If <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 r=3D0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle r=3D0}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/894a83e863728b4ee2e12f3a999a09f5f2bf1c89" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:5.31ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle r=3D=
0}"></span>, the region is known as the <b>punctured disk</b> (a <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disk_(mathematics)" title=3D"Disk (mathemati=
cs)">disk</a> with a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_(mathem=
atics)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Point (mathematics)">point</a> hole =
in the center) of radius <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span> around the=
 point <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i></span>.
</p><p>As a subset of the complex <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Plane_(mathematics)" title=3D"Plane (mathematics)">plane</a>, an annulus ca=
n be considered as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_surfa=
ce" title=3D"Riemann surface">Riemann surface</a>. The complex structure of=
 an annulus depends only on the ratio <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=
=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>r</i></span=
><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>R</i></span></span>=
=E2=81=A0</span></span>. Each annulus <span class=3D"texhtml">ann(<i>a</i>;=
 <i>r</i>, <i>R</i>)</span> can be <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Holomorphic_function" title=3D"Holomorphic function">holomorphically</a> m=
apped to a standard one centered at the origin and with outer radius 1 by t=
he map
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e z\mapsto {\frac {z-a}{R}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=A6<!-- =E2=86=A6 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
