            <mrow>
              <mi>z</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>a</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mi>R</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle z\mapsto {\fr=
ac {z-a}{R}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ed4a0f2edf0bf8420fb9a4da1c25aab581750fad" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:11.344ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle z\=
mapsto {\frac {z-a}{R}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The inner radius is then <span class=3D"texhtml"><link rel=3D"mw-dedupli=
cated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=
=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>r</i></span=
><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>R</i></span></span>=
=E2=81=A0</span> &lt; 1</span>.
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hadamard_three-circle_t=
heorem" title=3D"Hadamard three-circle theorem">Hadamard three-circle theor=
em</a> is a statement about the maximum value a holomorphic function may ta=
ke inside an annulus.
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joukowsky_transform" ti=
tle=3D"Joukowsky transform">Joukowsky transform</a> <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Conformal_map" title=3D"Conformal map">conformally maps</=
a> an annulus onto an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipse" tit=
le=3D"Ellipse">ellipse</a> with a slit cut between foci.
</p>
